SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 150
BY SENATOR FOIL
CONDOLENCES. To express sincere and heartfelt condolences upon the passing of Robert
H. "Bob" Baumann.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the
3 death of Robert H. "Bob" Baumann, longtime director of the Louisiana State
4 University Center for Energy Studies and trusted advisor on Louisiana energy policy.
5 WHEREAS, it was with deep regret and profound sorrow that the citizens of
6 Louisiana learned of the death of Robert H. "Bob" Baumann on Thursday, November 6,
7 2025, at the age of seventy-four; and
8 WHEREAS, it is fitting to express enduring gratitude for Bob Baumann's outstanding
9 contributions to this state, particularly during more than three decades of service to
10 Louisiana State University and to the industries that serve as the foundation of the Louisiana
11 economy; and
12 WHEREAS, born and raised in the Queens borough of New York City, Bob
13 Baumann graduated from the University of Rhode Island and arrived in Baton Rouge in
14 1974 to pursue graduate studies at Louisiana State University, where he earned his Master
15 of Science degree in geography in 1980 under Dr. Jess Walker, with a thesis examining the
16 interrelationships of marsh elevation, water level, sedimentation, and other selected variables
17 in the Lower Barataria Basin; and
18 WHEREAS, Bob Baumann fell in love with LSU and the Baton Rouge community
