1 and never returned to the northeast, putting down deep roots in Louisiana and devoting the
2 whole of his professional life to the people, institutions, and industries of this state; and
3 WHEREAS, Bob Baumann was a founding member of the LSU Center for Energy
4 Studies upon its establishment in 1982 and, over the course of his tenure, rose to lead the
5 center, building it into an indispensable source of energy information and analysis for the
6 legislature, public agencies, business and civic groups, and the academic community, and
7 there was no part of his long career of which he was more justifiably proud than his work
8 on behalf of Louisiana State University; and
9 WHEREAS, Bob Baumann served as a confidant, friend, and advisor to multiple
10 leaders of the LSU system, beginning with Chancellor James Wharton, who recognized his
11 quiet capability and brought him into his inner circle during the 1980s campaign to institute
12 more selective admission standards at the university; and
13 WHEREAS, Bob Baumann served for many years as LSU's representative at the state
14 capitol, earning the trust of legislators across the political spectrum and securing critical
15 support for the university's teaching, research, and outreach missions until his retirement
16 from LSU in 2007; and
17 WHEREAS, Bob Baumann's blend of intellectual rigor and steady, plain-spoken
18 clarity made him one of the most trusted voices on energy policy in the state; as Tyler Gray,
19 a director of the LSU Energy Institute, observed, Bob "authored influential research, advised
20 governors and legislatures, and shaped major debates with a calm, steady clarity that made
21 even the most complex oil and gas issues understandable" and was "a tremendous mentor
22 to generations of students, colleagues, and policymakers"; and
23 WHEREAS, in 2014, in recognition of a career spent bettering the working
24 environment of Louisiana's oil and gas industry, Bob Baumann received the Lifetime
25 Achievement Award of the Louisiana Independent Oil and Gas Association, becoming only
26 the third individual so honored in the association's history; and
27 WHEREAS, in 2023, the Louisiana Mid-Continent Oil and Gas Association
28 presented Bob Baumann with the Hard Hat Award in recognition of his exemplary and
29 outstanding contributions to Louisiana's oil and natural gas industry, an honor reflecting a
30 lifetime of service to the sector; and
