1 him; and
2 WHEREAS, above all, Bob Baumann was a devoted family man with an unwavering
3 commitment to his wife, Brenda, and their two sons, Frank and Kyle, and who will be
4 missed profoundly by his beloved family and the many other individuals whose lives he
5 touched with his wisdom and generosity of spirit; and
6 WHEREAS, with the death of Bob Baumann, the state has lost a faithful adopted son,
7 a builder of institutions, and a larger-than-life figure whose counsel shaped a generation of
8 Louisiana energy policy and whose absence will be felt at the Louisiana State Capitol every
9 day of every session to come.
10 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
11 does hereby express sincere and heartfelt condolences upon the death of Dr. Robert H. "Bob"
12 Baumann; does hereby recognize and record for posterity his notable accomplishments and
13 singular contributions to Louisiana State University, to the LSU Center for Energy Studies,
14 and to the broader cause of sound energy and industrial policy in this state; and does hereby
15 extend enduring appreciation for the pride and honor that he will forever bring to his family,
16 to LSU, to the Baton Rouge community, and to the state of Louisiana.
